insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_h1uss086',36,'Amazon','"The packaging of the product was good and received exactly as described and on the same delivery day. The design of the phone is quite impressive, I liked it. The amoled display is impressive with the dual speaker which is loud and decent. But the camera quality is not that good and I noticed the battery drains quickly as compared to my previous phone and heats up too. I also noticed slight lag in the UI sometimes ,other then that no issue at all and you can go for this phone. Around one hour,it almost full charges if we don''t use the phone while charging but it takes more time if we use the phone while charging. I hope the battery draining issue resolves soon in a new software update and the camera quality gets better too. Overall, it''s an Indian brand and we all should keep supporting to make a better future. Thankyou"',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_ha7dkpf',36,'Amazon','"For the price- it is a very good phone. Clean software, nice display, sufficient features. Although camera is average, but in my case it was never a priority. Battery life is decent but it''s been only a day so will test it more. Processor is good enough for daily tasks not gaming or high intensity activity. Design is nice. Headphone jack (3.5mm) is missing, it should have been given. As for software update (1 year). Security update (2 years) could have been more than 1 and 2 years. I would recommend this phone for daily use and heavy tasks. The amazon service has gotten worse in the few past years. I ordered this phone on 14 may it showed delivery on 20 may, but when I completed the payment the delivery date changed to 26 may. Phone was dispatched on 21 may evening. Although I got it on 25 a day before the changed delivery date. The delivery experience was not good at all, had me worried if I was going to get the phone itself or not. Everybody knows how many types of scams are going on in our country."',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_hwv30rq',36,'Amazon','"This phone is just amazing! in this price range. I was worried at first and could not find much review online of this phone and its photo but I purchased it just by looking at its features. It has a good processor, enough ram (6Gb) and moderate cameras. Front camera provides good selfie in day in good light but not very clear in dim light. It''s amazing how they have bundled together so many features in this price range. I tried playing NFS game it runs smoothly. Display is HDR supported tried on youtube hdr videos. It was launched in April, 2026 so it has around 2 years of system updates. I really wish Lava tops the market in future. Thank you lava for bringing this amazing phone."',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_hpzmby3',36,'Amazon','"Other than some heating issues in the peak summer months, everything other is more than expected. I can''t imagine this display, speaker, and processor in this price. The display, performance, speaker, everything is good. Even the camera is decent as of its price. I loved the background stream feature and the in display fingerprint sensor is working well. Appearance is good but i would suggest buying the black one ignoring the official images. Charging and battery is same as stated, easily lasts one day."',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_h146f2jq',36,'Amazon','"This is a very good product for the price . It''s slim and light weight but build is good . Its display is good and day to day task is easy . Little slow to respond but still good enough .it came with a BIS certified fast charger and cable , both are of very good quality . Specially the power cable is thick and durable 👌.overall very happy with purchase till now . I bought it for navigation on motorcycle, will wait and see how it performs. Big thumbs up 👍 to team lava and make in India 🇮🇳!"',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_hjknd72',36,'Amazon','"Considering the Price and the specs that this brand offered is what many brand lacks now a days solely for cost-cuttings, and fit themselves in a specific price bracket with definitely low features than this one. Punch-Hole Amoled Display, Indisplay fingerprint sensor, Android 15 out of box with Android 16 Assured and 2 years of security patch software updates, 50 MP rear camera which gives good quality photos, 8 MP front average quality photos, the processor is great for normal everyday tasks without any lags or gitters, battery and the 33w fast charging is great at this price. Overall a great device to consider under this budget of 11500-12500 price bracket. I''m a Galaxy S24 Ultra user, for me the software and camera are the top priorities, I found this phone perfectly fitting in bridging the gap between low range and mid range phones. Few things I didn''t liked in terms of software more refinement is needed to organize it more categorically. For other things, basic software level fine tuning with future updates would definitely turn this phone as a budget best. Got to know this a rebranded version of previously launched phone Lava Blaze Amoled 2. Don''t know why they have to rebrand it again as Lava Bold 2. Rest, currently I''m testing the phone very minutely in day-to-day real world scenarios. I''ll further tune this review accordingly and add HQ Pictures after a week or so."',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
insert into comments (id,model_id,source,comment_text,comment_date) values ('Amazon_36_h1rh3t99',36,'Amazon','"Looking at the price theres not much to complain. Its just that i didnt find the camera good. Although i am not sure how cameras are supposed to be in this proce range. Low light photos are grainy and not sharp. Also i feel that they should also give better battery packs. Since everyone''s goving 6-7k mah"',NULL) on conflict (id) do nothing;
